versiononly)Financial crises caused by any combination of many factors are:
* Simple and unpredictable market forces (conversions of asset value to price) that torpedo a group of companies
* Chaos in the economy (banks closing, credit default swaps, sellable securities, default swaps stashing in other countries); 
* Extractive stress disorder (buying bad mortgages, selling bad securities, infilling with junk); 
* Immigration restrictions, or restrictions on movement of people and technology across borders (yield more people on the same loan, increase cost of acquiring new skills, increase pressure on banks to reduce balance sheets);
